Description: pychord
        =======
        
        |Build Status|
        
        Overview
        --------
        
        Pychord is a python library to handle musical chords.
        
        Installation
        ------------
        
        .. code:: sh
        
            $ pip install pychord
        
        Usage
        -----
        
        Create a Chord
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
        
        .. code:: python
        
            >>> from pychord import Chord
            >>> c = Chord("Am7")
            >>> c
            <Chord: Am7>
            >>> c.info()
            """
            Am7
            root=A
            quality=m7
            appended=[]
            on=None
            """
        
        Transpose a Chord
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
        
        .. code:: python
        
            >>> c = Chord("Am7/G")
            >>> c.transpose(3)
            >>> c
            <Chord: Cm7/Bb>
        
        Get component notes
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
        
        .. code:: python
        
            >>> c = Chord("Am7")
            >>> c.components()
            ['A', 'C', 'E', 'G']
        
        Create chord progressions
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
        
        .. code:: python
        
            >>> from pychord import ChordProgression
            >>> cp = ChordProgression(["C", "G/B", "Am"])
            >>> cp
            <ChordProgression: C | G/B | Am>
        
            >>> cp.append("Em/G")
            >>> cp
            <ChordProgression: C | G/B | Am | Em/G>
        
            >>> cp.transpose(+3)
            >>> cp
            <ChordProgression: Eb | Bb/D | Cm | Gm/Bb>
        
        Supported Python Versions
        -------------------------
        
        -  2.7
        -  3.3 and above
        
